{
  "text": "Parts (a) through (e) of this assumption have antecedents in the previous literature. Parts (a), (d) and (e) are similar to parts (ii), (iii), (iv) respectively of Theorem 2 (LAD with random regressors) of [CITATION_1] . Part (b) states linearity of the conditional quantile function and requires a bound on the components of the possibly infinite-dimensional coefficient vector. Part (c) is analogous to the error assumption of [CITATION_2] , and embodies the common requirement that the density of the error exist and be continuous at a particular point (typically 0).",
